    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>Tales From Aloft</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Robert L Wolke letter on June 25 travel article says he pushes forward tilted airline seats when passenger in front gets up or leans forward (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor: Regarding ''How to Survive Economy Class'' (June 25): I have discovered a way to fight back against the person in front of me who keeps the seat tilted back all the way. I wait for the passenger to go to the toilet, or even to lean forward for a few seconds, and then I quickly push the seatback forward several inches. It moves easily. Nobody has yet noticed the difference.</p>
        <p>ROBERT L. WOLKE  Pittsburgh</p>
      </block>
